org.bytedeco.arrow

Class Status

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bytedeco.javacpp.Pointer
      • org.bytedeco.arrow.Status
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    @Namespace(value="arrow")
 @NoOffset
 @Properties(inherit=arrow.class)
public class Status
extends Pointer
    \brief Status outcome object (success or error) The Status object is an object holding the outcome of an operation. The outcome is represented as a StatusCode, either success (StatusCode::OK) or an error (any other of the StatusCode enumeration values). Additionally, if an error occurred, a specific error message is generally attached.
